Done ** Study done in upland portions of the Park, but doesn't give elevation. Coordinates were calculated using a mapping website. It reports habitat as Forest. Elevation values for Santa Rosa NP taken from IUCN Directory of Neotropical Protected Areas= 0 to 319 mt. IUCN Directory give a set of coordinates, but not very accurate, these coord point out a different site "Estacion Experimental Forestal Horizontes" which is a research station southeast of Santa Rosa NP.
Comments: Data taken from Fleming, T. H. 1988. Authors reported the study site in upland portions of the Park, however a specific elevation value is not mentioned. Elevation values reported for Parque Nacional Santa Rosa at Bat Eco-Interactions are those reported by The IUCN Directory of Neotropical Protected Areas.
Citation Short Description: Fleming, T. H. & C. F. Williams. 1990
